    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7">
            <p class="mb-0 font-weight-bold science-head">• Is it Hair Loss or Hair Fall ?</p>
            <p class="text-left science-text">Hair fall is when you daily lose 50-100 strands of hair. Whereas, hair loss is hair fall that will not go away.
                Hair fall that happens for over a month is hair loss,more precisely a hair loss condition.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0 mt-3 font-weight-bold science-head">• Why am I losing 50-100 strands of hair ? </p>
            <p class="text-left science-text">It is because hair grows in phases:</p>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ml-0 my-3">
              <li class="list-group-item pl-0 py-1 science-text"><b class="font-weight-bold">Anagen</b> The growth phase LASTS 2 TO 8 YRS </li>
              <li class="list-group-item pl-0 py-1 science-text"><b class="font-weight-bold">Catagen</b> Transition phase LASTS 10 DAYS</li>
              <li class="list-group-item pl-0 py-1 science-text"><b class="font-weight-bold">Telogen</b> Resting phase LASTS AROUND THREE MONTHS</li>
              <li class="list-group-item pl-0 py-1 science-text"><b class="font-weight-bold">Exogen</b> New hair phase THE SHEDDING OF OLD HAIR AND GROWTH OF NEW HAIR</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-left science-text">A single strand of hair passes through all four stages, Normally 90% of the hair is in the anagen or
                growth phase and the rest are either in the resting or shedding phase. In case of a hair loss condition, each hair cycle
                produces thinner, weaker and fewer hair that eventually leads to baldness.
            </p>
        </div>
