        <p class="science-second-text">3. Alopecia Areata</p>
        <p class="science-text">This is technically an autoimmune  disorder, in which your body’s immune system  starts attacking your follicles as if they are foreign particles. The hair loss is in the form of a coin  sized circular bald patch with no hair on it. In extreme cases, the hair loss is not limited to your scalp and may also occur in other parts of the body.  
